# invalidClientProcess

**Type Property**

An error indicating that an invalid client process reported the incoming call.

## Declaration

```swift
static var invalidClientProcess: CXErrorCodeNotificationServiceExtensionError.Code { get }
```

## Discussion

Only call the [doc://com.apple.callkit/documentation/CallKit/CXProvider/reportNewIncomingVoIPPushPayload(_:completion:)] method from a [doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/UserNotifications/UNNotificationServiceExtension] object that is responding to an incoming notification request.

## Understanding Error Codes

- **missingNotificationFilteringEntitlement**: An error indicating that the notification service extension is missing the required filtering entitlement.
- **unknown**: An error that occurs when there is an unknown problem.
- **CXErrorCodeNotificationServiceExtensionError.Code**: Constants for errors returned when reporting new, incoming VoIP calls.
